Proxy

Acts as an interface to something else.

Concepts
* Interface by wrapping
* can add functionality
* security, Simplicity, Remote call, Cost
* Proxy is called to access the real object

Example
* java.lang.reflect.Proxy

Design
* Interface based
* Interface and iplementation class
* java.lang.reflect.InvocationHandler, java.lang.reflect.Proxy

Client, interface InvocationHandler, Proxy and RealObject


Pitfalls
* Only one proxy
* Another Abstraction
* Similar to other patterns

Contrast
Proxy
* can add functionality, but its not its main purpose
* can only have one
* compile time

Decorator
* Dynamically adds functionality
* Chained pattern
* decorator points to its own type
* Runtime

Summary

